Senate President, Bukola Saraki has advised state house of assemblies to pass a bill that will suspend payment of pension to former governors and deputy governors. The senate president made this appeal on Wednesday when he commended the speaker of Kwara state house of assembly Ali Ahmad, for working to ensure that the bill was passed in Kwara State. “I am pleased that following my conversation with Kwara speaker, Rt. Hon. Ali Ahmad, two months ago, the bill to suspend the payment of pension to former governors and their deputies when they hold a political or public office was passed into law yesterday by the Kwara house of assembly” Saraki said “Moving forward, it is my hope that other state assemblies take a cue from Kwara state and pass similar pieces of Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook